<br>
Cleric - Necro - ShadowKnight (Dark Elf)<br>
Shaman - Necro - ShadowKnight (Iksar)<br>
Shaman - Necro - Beastlord (Iksar)<br>
Shaman - Bard - Warrior (Vah Shir)<br>
Shaman - Necro - Warrior (Iksar)<br>
Cleric - Palladin - Magician (HEF)<br>
Shaman - Monk - Warrior (Iksar)<br>
Enchanter - Magician - Shaman (Sorry!) (Mixxed Race but no good-bad combo)<br>
<br>
I personally like all caster groups.  I would opt for Necro - Magician - Enchanter any day as I've done this before and it totally rocks.  Talk about you can levle from 1 - 60 no problem (Slow Rules).  The reason why you want the same race or good/bad affiliation is so all you guys can travel together and not have to worry about anyone being KOS.  Porting is overrated now with PoP so don't even worry about that.  I would personally go with the CLeric - Necro - SK combo since the Necro can also heal and slow undeads, not to mention crowd control like Root - Undead Charm - Screaming Terror, etc.  The Necro also has a pet to help in melee and the SK can (if he learns well) pull good with Snare and FD.  Sorry to mention Enchanters, but how else do you plan to keep the Cleric's mana up with the KEI nerf if you don't have an Enchanter.  Just a Cleric - Warr - Enc combo can to from 1 - 60 easily and fast with the new exp bonus changes. <p><center>a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=729398" target="_new">View My Ub3r Gear</a><br><img src="http://equb3r.tripod.com/new_sig.jpg" /></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=arkayoop>ArkayOoP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Parkay</span><br>  Posts: 1377<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(7/28/03 9:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernclassdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=263.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.orderofthephoenix.com/images/signature/biguglydorf..Arkay.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Trio?</span><hr size=1> Could really do any combination and come out decent actually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrnta